{"word":"ἀρνός","slug":"ἀρνός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀρνός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>Prob. akin to <el>ἔριον, εἶρος</el>, <i>wool</i>.\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a lamb</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>agnus, agna</el>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a sheep</i>, whether <i>ram</i> or <i>ewe</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}